## Plan

**Approach:** Add two read-only subcommands — `etude retro list` and `etude retro show <id>` — to the existing `retro` parent command, modelled directly on `etude run list`/`run show` (internal/cli/run.go). They walk the already-shipped, already-allowlisted `refs/etude/retros/*` namespace via refstore.List/Resolve/ReadFile and parse the same runmanifest.Manifest the q87 writer produces (Workflow=retro, one `retro` stage, role:retro markdown Output, indexed subject_run.N/bead.N + flat scope/trigger/decision/supersedes/gate.1/bench.1/eval.1 Refs). The one deliberate divergence from `run show`: `retro show` DUMPS the markdown body inline (the body IS the retro), which `run show` never does (it prints only artifact-path metadata) — design §2 Phase B says retro show 'wants a body dump that run show lacks'. No new schema, no new namespace, no writer/mutation, no generate/triggers/config (that is etude-n0t, deferred).

**Files:**
- internal/cli/retro.go - MODIFY: register the two new subcommands on the existing newRetroCommand parent (cmd.AddCommand(newRetroListCommand(...)), newRetroShowCommand(...)); add a retroShowListRunner{store, stdout} mirroring runShowListRunner. Keep it in this file (q87 keeps capture here; run.go keeps run list+show+printRunDetail together — one file per parent command is the repo convention).
- internal/cli/retro.go - ADD: retroListRunner.list() — refstore.List over retrosPrefix (refs/etude/retros), TrimPrefix each ref, ReadFile manifest.json, ParseJSON, render a tabwriter table. Header: RETRO ID | SCOPE | TRIGGER | SUBJECTS | CREATED (mirrors design §2 Phase B columns). SCOPE/TRIGGER from Refs[scope]/Refs[trigger]; SUBJECTS = count or comma-join of indexed subject_run.N + bead.N (sorted by index); CREATED = manifest.Created RFC3339 UTC. Empty -> 'no retros found', exit 0 (mirror 'no runs found'). Corrupt/missing manifest -> error naming the retro id, nothing to stdout (mirror run list).
- internal/cli/retro.go - ADD: retroShowRunner.show(id) — validateCLIIdentifier('retro id', id) + retro.IsValidRetroID(id) guard (mirror validateRunIDExtra); Resolve refs/etude/retros/<id>, map refstore.ErrNotFound -> 'retro "<id>" not found'; ReadFile+ParseJSON manifest; render header (retro id/scope/trigger/decision/supersedes/created), sorted subjects (subject_run.N then bead.N), gate/bench/eval refs, producer (harness/model/skill from the single retro stage), then read the Output body via store.ReadFile(ref, stage.Output.Path) and print it inline under a '--- retro body ---' divider. Storage is always content (capture uses AddContent), so a direct ReadFile dump is correct; guard non-content storage by printing the artifact path instead.
- internal/cli/retro_test.go - MODIFY: add TestRetroList* (zero/one/many+lexical order/corrupt-manifest) and TestRetroShow* (existing happy path incl. body dump + subjects + scope/trigger/decision, unknown id, invalid id before git) mirroring run_test.go. Reuse existing helpers initCaptureRepo/writeFile/chdir/execute and the existing retro capture path to seed retros.
- docs/cli/etude_retro_list.md, docs/cli/etude_retro_show.md - GENERATED by `make docs` (gen-docs auto-walks the command tree). Must be committed.
- cmd/gen-docs/main_test.go - MODIFY: add 'etude_retro_list.md' and 'etude_retro_show.md' to expectedCommands (and, since q87 left them out, optionally 'etude_retro.md'/'etude_retro_capture.md' — but keep 1-bead scope: add at minimum the two new pages). Add a checks entry for the two new pages.
- docs/run.md is the model for a hand-written user doc, but README.md already advertises `retro` (top-level) and docs/README.md already indexes it at cli/etude_retro.md, so docs-reality-check already passes for the parent. A dedicated hand-written docs/retro.md is OPTIONAL polish, not required by the docs gate; recommend updating the existing docs/README.md Retro line to mention list/show, plus a short list/show section if a hand doc is wanted. Decide during Docs phase.

**Tests:**
- retro list: zero retros -> 'no retros found' + exit 0; one retro -> header columns present + a data row with id/scope/trigger/subject-count/RFC3339-Z created; multiple -> lexical order by id; corrupt manifest -> non-zero, names id, nothing on stdout.
- retro show: existing retro renders id/scope/trigger/decision/created + indexed subjects in order + the inline markdown body bytes (round-trips capture); unknown id -> 'retro "<id>" not found' non-zero; invalid id (slash/.. /.lock) rejected before any git call.
- Round-trip: seed via `retro capture` in the test repo, then list+show, asserting the read side reproduces exactly what the writer stored (Workflow/stage/Output role + Refs).
- Edge cases: workflow-scope retro (no subject_run) lists with empty/zero SUBJECTS; multi-subject cohort shows all subject_run.N + bead.N sorted; --ref custom keys do not break rendering.

**Docs:**
- REQUIRED: regenerate docs/cli via `make docs` (adds etude_retro_list.md + etude_retro_show.md) and extend cmd/gen-docs/main_test.go expectedCommands. Run `make docs-check` and `make docs-reality` — both must stay green.
- OPTIONAL: extend docs/README.md Retro index line / add a docs/retro.md list+show section mirroring docs/run.md. Not gate-required since `retro` is already advertised; decide in Docs phase.

**Risks:** Low. Read-only, mirrors run list/show over an already-shipped+allowlisted namespace; no schema/namespace/writer changes. Only subtlety is the deliberate inline body dump (the one place retro show diverges from run show) and refactoring shared header/stage rendering: per design open-issue, FACTOR shared rendering out of printRunDetail rather than forking it — but keep that refactor minimal and within run.go/retro.go to stay 1-commit; if factoring printRunDetail risks touching run show output/tests, prefer a small retro-local renderer and note the shared-rendering follow-up. Generated-doc + gen-docs test sync is a known checklist item, not a risk.

**Gate tier:** Tier 2 (Opus + codex). Read-only product CLI modeled directly on run list/run show over an already-shipped namespace; no new schema, namespace, or mutation. The only judgement calls (inline body dump; whether to refactor printRunDetail vs a local renderer) are local and low-blast-radius — they do not rise to Tier 1.

